cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel fully Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture for the automatic segmentation of retinal layer structures in OCT imaging. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of dilated residual blocks and an asymmetric U-shape configuration suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The application of the method to highly pathological eyes indicates a potential interest in medical imaging (cs.MM). Finally, the use of a neural network for segmentation suggests a possible interest in neural networks (cs.NE).
